article.headline: Colorado 76, Ark.-Pine Bluff 56
article.story: BOULDER, CO -- Colorado got 14 points from sophomore Casey Crawford and 13 from freshman Austin Dufault to beat Arkansas-Pine Bluff 76-56 Friday night in the season opener for both teams. With 10 underclassmen on its roster -- five freshmen and five sophomores -- Colorado headed into the season with one of the youngest teams in school history, and youth figured prominently in the Buffaloes strong start. Nate Tomlinson, part of a starting lineup that included two freshmen, two sophomores and a junior, added 12 points in his first college game. Cory Higgins also had 12 points for Colorado, which opened a 40-20 halftime lead. Colorado outscored the Golden Lions 19-5 over the final 7:07 of the first session with Tomlinson, Higgins and Crawford all hitting 3's during the run. Lebaron Weathers led Arkansas-Pine Bluff with 22 points. Tavaris Washington added 18 points despite fouling out with 4:27 remaining.
